 <span class="birthstoneinfoheader">Alternate Birthstone</span>
<p  >The lapis lazuli, a pretty and versatile gemstone is considered to be an alternate birthstone for people born in September. Its name is derived from Latin term 'lapis' which means stone and Persian word 'lazhward' which means blue rock. It is a soft stone with a value of 5 on the Mohs scale. The color is strong blue with minute hint of violet. Best quality of this gemstone is mined in Afghanistan but it is also found in Siberia, Chile, the U.S., Pakistan, and Canada.It is popularly worn as a charm to safeguard against health problems. It also promotes calm, sound sleep. It is given to commemorate the 7th and 9th wedding anniversary. </p>
